news.title: Gurugram: DTCP razes six illegal colonies, frees 15-acre agriculture land
news.para: During the demolition, people gathered at the site and DTCP officials appealed to them that they should not invest their hard earned money in such unauthorised colonies and should contact the office of DTP for any enquiry before buying a land/plot.

news.title: Delhi: On the ground, regularisation plans evoke mixed reactions
news.para: Situated close to Geeta Colony and Krishna Nagar, East Azad Nagar has narrow lanes lined with shops selling food, clothes and grocery. There are four- and five-storey residential flats along the main road.

news.title: Pune cantonment board warns against illegal property sale
news.para: Subrat Pal, the CEO of PCB, told TOI, “The notice has been issued after we noticed the illegal sale of old grant bungalows (OGBs) in the PCB limits in the last few years.”

news.title: Tamil Nadu: Income tax department raids seven places belonging to realty firms, businessmen
news.para: The searches were held on 10 premises at Aminjikarai, Anna Nagar, Egmore, and Kilpauk in Chennai, while in Coimbatore the searches were held at seven places. Armed paramilitary personnel stood guard at entry and exit points of those premises.

news.title: Over 43,000 commercial establishments in Pimpri Chinchwad fail fire safety test
news.para: A total of 43,925 commercial establishments — including hospitals, educational institutes, shops and industrial units — have been surveyed so far, and almost all of them lack compliance to fire safety rules.

news.title: Over 2,000 residential plots near airport? Yamuna Authority starts survey
news.para: According to officials, the survey work would be completed in 15 days. Subsequently, the Authority will expedite the process of purchasing land for these sectors.

news.title: Entire Aarey a 'green zone' as Maharashtra extends cover to last 326 acres
news.para: The move makes virtually the entire Aarey a green zone and lays to rest any doubts about the protected status of the 445-hectare (1,100-acre) colony, one of the few remaining lungs of the city.

news.title: Godrej Properties' subsidiary receives GST demand and penalty order worth Rs 22.54 crore
news.para: Oasis Landmarks LLP will challenge the order at the appropriate forum in accordance with the law and there is no material impact of the same on financial, operations or other activities of the company.

news.title: Goa government announces single-window clearance for land allotment, construction of industries
news.para: Chief Minister Pramod Sawant held a meeting with the Goa Chamber of Commerce and Industries (GCCI), Confederation of Indian Industries (CII), Goa State Industries Association (GSIA) and others.

news.title: MahaRERA’s action on non-compliance prompts increase in quarterly project updates
news.para: The strict action initiated by the regulator has prompted more than 222 projects or 46.25% out of 480 projects registered in the month of April 2023 to file their quarterly updates within the stipulated time limit.

news.title: Settl raises Rs 10 crore in pre-series A round from Gruhas, We Founder Circle, others
news.para: Anthill Ventures, Inflection Point Ventures, Ah! ventures, Nila Spaces, Soonicorn Ventures, Awficacy Capital, Pai Ventures LLP and Ekyum also participated in the Pre Series A round.

news.title: Nagpur district planning committee okays draft plan of Rs 669 crore for 2024-25
news.para: The DPC approved ₹668.72 crore for the year 2024-25 in a meeting held on Monday. An additional fund of ₹1,431 crore too was demanded. The total demand of the district is pegged at ₹2,100 crore.

news.title: About 40% industry land not in Greater Noida development body's kitty
news.para: Even as the Authority has a land bank of 645 acres available to allot plots to more than 340 allottees, officials informed that the Authority has freed 56 acres in the past six months and allotted some parts in new residential schemes.

news.title: Hyderabad's airport metro, Pharma City not scrapped: Telangana CM
news.para: In other words, the Congress government might not take up Raidurg-Shamshabad Airport Metro line project as planned by the previous BRS government.

news.title: Three decades of excellence in Power, Infra and Real Estate: In conversation with Manish Agrawal, MD, Omicron Group
news.para: Our interview covers the remarkable journey of entrepreneurship by the Omicron Group from Power to Grade-A Commercial Real Estate in Pune by Mr. Manish Agrawal, Managing Director, Omicron Business Landmarks.

news.title: Now, e-stamping for property registration at Uttar Pradesh post offices
news.para: Launched as a pilot project following an agreement between the department of Post and Stock Holding Corporation of India Limited, the facility is expected to curb black marketing and overcharging of stamps.

news.title: Concerns over illegal houses in Old Goa
news.para: Heritage activist Prajal Sakhardande said that discussions with the state archaeology department revealed that no permissions were sought for these constructions.

news.title: Indore-Ujjain division sees 6.5% rise in revenue from property registration
news.para: Districts, especially Agar-Malwa, Shajapur, Khargone, Indore, Ujjain and Alirajpur, saw a considerable rise in property registrations that earned the stamp and registrar department around Rs 250 crore, 6.5% more revenue in 2023 compared to 2022 calendar year, senior officials concerned said.

news.title: Mixed reactions over new Bhubaneswar development body's property rules
news.para: The BDA said anyone already having a house allotted from any government agency in the city will no longer be eligible to get a house from the BDA.

news.title: Homebuyers urge MahaRERA to build regulations to ensure construction quality
news.para: On December 4, the authority had floated a consultation paper seeking public suggestions on its proposed regulatory framework.
